 1 | # ArduHumanoid SITL - Bipedal Walking Robot for ArduPilot
 2 | 
 3 | [![Gazebo Harmonic](https://img.shields.io/badge/Gazebo-Harmonic-blue)](https://gazebosim.org)
 4 | [![ArduPilot Rover](https://img.shields.io/badge/ArduPilot-Rover-green)](https://ardupilot.org)
 5 | [![GSoC 2026](https://img.shields.io/badge/GSoC-2026-orange)](https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com)
 6 | 
 7 | ## Overview
 8 | 
 9 | A minimal humanoid vehicle type running on ArduPilot Rover SITL — proving ArduPilot can command a bipedal humanoid to walk via Gazebo Harmonic simulation. Built in SDF 1.9 following the official ArduPilot legged robot pattern from [ardupilot_gazebo](https://github.com/ArduPilot/ardupilot_gazebo) and [SITL_Models](https://github.com/ArduPilot/SITL_Models).
10 | 
11 | ## Architecture
12 | 
13 | ```
14 | Gazebo Harmonic (8-DOF SDF humanoid)
15 |          ↓ IMU + pose (JSON)
16 | ArduPilot Rover SITL (EKF3 sensor fusion)
17 |          ↓ SRV_Channels (Lua scripting)
18 | humanoid.lua (ZMP IK + gait controller)
19 |          ↓ servo PWM
20 | ArduPilotPlugin → joints move → robot walks
21 |          ↑
22 | MAVLink GUIDED/LOITER/AUTO (waypoint navigation)
23 | ```
24 | 
25 | ## Quick Start
26 | 
27 | ```bash
28 | # Terminal 1 — Gazebo
29 | export GZ_SIM_RESOURCE_PATH=$HOME/ardupilot_gazebo/models:$GZ_SIM_RESOURCE_PATH
30 | gz sim -v4 ~/ardupilot_gazebo/worlds/humanoid.sdf
31 | 
32 | # Terminal 2 — ArduPilot Rover SITL
33 | mkdir -p ~/ardupilot/Rover/scripts
34 | cp scripts/humanoid.lua ~/ardupilot/Rover/scripts/
35 | cd ~/ardupilot/Rover
36 | sim_vehicle.py -v Rover --model JSON --console
37 | 
38 | # Enable Lua scripting (first run only)
39 | # In MAVProxy: param set SCR_ENABLE 1
40 | # Then reboot, then arm to start walking
41 | # MANUAL> arm throttle
42 | ```
43 | 
44 | ## Robot Specifications
45 | 
46 | | Property      | Value                  |
47 | |---------------|------------------------|
48 | | Total Mass    | 3.9 kg                 |
49 | | Active DOF    | 8 (4 per leg)          |
50 | | Leg Geometry  | L1=L2=0.20m symmetric  |
